        ]
      },
      "text": [
        " قُلْتُ لِأَبِي الْحَسَنِ ( عليه السلام ) إِنَّ عِنْدَنَا قَوْماً لَهُمْ مَحَبَّةٌ وَ لَيْسَتْ لَهُمْ تِلْكَ الْعَزِيمَةُ يَقُولُونَ بِهَذَا الْقَوْلِ فَقَالَ لَيْسَ أُولَئِكَ مِمَّنْ عَاتَبَ اللَّهُ إِنَّمَا قَالَ اللَّهُ فَاعْتَبِرُوا يا أُولِي الْأَبْصارِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "And from him, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Ibn Fazzal, from Al Hassan Bin Al Jahm who said, ",
          "‘I said to Abu Al-Hassan<sup>asws</sup>, ‘In our presence there is a group of people, for them is love, and there isn’t that magnificence for them that they should be saying with this word (Al-Wilayah)’. So he<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘They are from the ones whom Allah<sup>azwj</sup> Admonished. But rather, Allah<sup>azwj</sup> Said <span class=\"ibTxt\"><a href=\"/#/books/quran:59#h2\"><a href=\"/books/quran:59#h2\">[59:2]</a></a> therefore take a lesson, O you who have vision</span>’."
        ]
      }
    }
  },
